                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            },
            {
                "name": "Had",
                "url": "/topics/had"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/ron_chernow_290840",
        "quote": "I think one of the important things that's happened in the course of the century is that life expectancy has doubled.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Ron Chernow",
            "url": "/quotes/ron_chernow_290840"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Think",
                "url": "/topics/think"
            },
            {
                "name": "I Think",
                "url": "/topics/i_think"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/ron_chernow_290841",
        "quote": "The public has lost faith in the ability of Social Security and Medicare to provide for old age. They've lost faith in the banking system and in conventional medical insurance.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Ron Chernow",
            "url": "/quotes/ron_chernow_290841"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Medical",
                "url": "/topics/medical"
            },
            {
                "name": "Insurance",
                "url": "/topics/insurance"
            },
            {
                "name": "Social",
                "url": "/topics/social"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/ron_chernow_290842",
        "quote": "There is a kind of fear, approaching a panic, that's spreading through the Baby Boom Generation, which has suddenly discovered that it will have to provide for its own retirement.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Ron Chernow",
            "url": "/quotes/ron_chernow_290842"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Generation",
                "url": "/topics/generation"
            },
            {
                "name": "Through",
                "url": "/topics/through"
            },
            {
                "name": "Which",
                "url": "/topics/which"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/ron_chernow_290844",
        "quote": "The Great Inflation of the 1970s destroyed faith in paper assets, because if you held a bond, suddenly the bond was worth much less money than it was before.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Ron Chernow",
            "url": "/quotes/ron_chernow_290844"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Before",
                "url": "/topics/before"
            },
            {
                "name": "Held",
                "url": "/topics/held"
            },
            {
                "name": "Less Money",
                "url": "/topics/less_money"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/ron_chernow_290845",
        "quote": "By the late 1980s people realized that houses did not always appreciate and that they could fluctuate like any other market commodity.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Ron Chernow",
            "url": "/quotes/ron_chernow_290845"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Always",
                "url": "/topics/always"
            },
            {
                "name": "Other",
                "url": "/topics/other"
            },
            {
                "name": "Commodity",
                "url": "/topics/commodity"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/ron_chernow_290846",
        "quote": "In the 1970s we saw a massive shift of household savings from the banks to the brokerage firms.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Ron Chernow",
            "url": "/quotes/ron_chernow_290846"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Banks",
                "url": "/topics/banks"
            },
            {
                "name": "Brokerage",
                "url": "/topics/brokerage"
            },
            {
                "name": "Massive",
                "url": "/topics/massive"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/ron_chernow_290847",
        "quote": "Once the brokerage house, rather than the bank, became the locus for American savings, that money would find its way into the stock market, because the broker was someone with a much higher tolerance for risk than the banker.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Ron Chernow",
            "url": "/quotes/ron_chernow_290847"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "American",
                "url": "/topics/american"
            },
            {
                "name": "Rather",
                "url": "/topics/rather"
            },
            {
                "name": "Became",
                "url": "/topics/became"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/ron_chernow_290852",
        "quote": "When the market is just going up, up, and up, we all tend to be blind to the holes in the market. They're all papered over by the rise.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Ron Chernow",
            "url": "/quotes/ron_chernow_290852"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Blind",
                "url": "/topics/blind"
